{
  "texts": [
    "II.Bias and Fairness in AI Algorithms: Bias in data: Bias in data can show up in several forms.",
    "Here are the top offenders: Historical bias is the already existing bias in the world that has seeped into our data.",
    "This bias can occur even given perfect sampling environments and feature selection, and tends to show up for groups that have been historically disadvantaged or excluded.",
    "Historical bias is illustrated by the 2016 paper \"Man is to Computer Programmer as Woman is to Homemaker,\" whose authors showed that word embeddings trained on Google News articles exhibit and in fact perpetuate gender-based stereotypes in society [40].",
    "Representation bias is a bit differentthis happens from the way we define and sample a population to create a dataset."
  ]
}